&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#149; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
&lt;div id='EdgarSAA123457890000' style=font-family : 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=font-size: 10pt; line-height: 115%; margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 &amp;#150; STOCK BASED COMPENSATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;On August 5, 2011, the Board of Directors approved the Company's 2011 Equity Compensation Plan (the &amp;#147;2011 Plan&amp;#148;). The 2011 Plan authorizes the issuance of various forms of stock-based awards, including incentive or non-qualified options, restricted stock awards, performance shares and other securities as described in greater detail in the 2011 Plan, to the Company's employees, officers, directors and consultants. A total of &lt;font&gt;20,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares are authorized for issuance under the 2011 Plan, which has not been approved by the stockholders of the Company as of January 31, 2015 a total of &lt;font&gt;16,333,333&lt;/font&gt; shares are available for issuance under the 2011 Plan.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;On October 14, 2012, the Board of Directors approved the Company's 2012 Equity Incentive Plan, which was amended and restated on September 19, 2013 (as amended and restated, the &amp;#147;2012 Plan&amp;#148;). The 2012 Plan authorizes the issuance of various forms of stock-based awards, including incentive or non-qualified options, restricted stock awards, restricted units, stock appreciation rights, performance shares and other securities as described in greater detail in the 2012 Plan, to the Company's employees, officers, directors and consultants. A total of &lt;font&gt;12,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares are authorized for issuance under the 2012 Plan, which has been approved by the stockholders of the Company, and as of January 31, 2015, a total of &lt;font&gt;60,717&lt;/font&gt; shares are available for issuance under the 2012 Plan.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;On September 10, 2013, the Board of Directors approved the Company's 2013 Equity Incentive Plan (the &amp;#147;2013 Plan&amp;#148;). The 2013 Plan authorizes the issuance of various forms of stock-based awards, including incentive or non-qualified options, restricted stock awards, restricted units, stock appreciation rights, performance shares and other securities as described in greater detail in the 2013 Plan, to the Company's employees, officers, directors and consultants. A total of &lt;font&gt;12,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares are authorized for issuance under the 2013 Plan, which has been approved by the stockholders of the Company to date, and as of January 31, 2015, a total of &lt;font&gt;3,341,038&lt;/font&gt; shares are available for issuance under the 2013 Plan.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;The Plans are administered by the Board of Directors in its discretion. The Board of Directors interprets the Plans and has broad discretion to select the eligible persons to whom awards will be granted, as well as the type, size and terms and conditions of each award, including the exercise price of stock options, the number of shares subject to awards, the expiration date of awards, and the vesting schedule or other restrictions applicable to awards.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;Activity in options during the year ended January 31, 2015 and related balances outstanding as of that date are set forth below:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-left: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
&lt;div id='EdgarSAA123457890000' style=font-family : 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10 - WARRANTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;&gt;Transaction with Mother Parkers&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; On April 24, 2014, the Company entered into a Subscription Agreement with Mother Parkers Tea &amp;amp; Coffee Inc.&amp;#160;(&amp;#147;Mother Parkers&amp;#148; and the &amp;#147;Subscription&amp;#148;).&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Pursuant to the Subscription, Mother Parkers purchased &lt;font&gt;7,333,529&lt;/font&gt; units from the Company, each consisting of (a) &lt;font&gt;one&lt;/font&gt; share of the Company's common stock, $&lt;font&gt;0.001&lt;/font&gt; par value per share (the &amp;#147;Shares&amp;#148;); and (b) &lt;font&gt;one&lt;/font&gt; (1) warrant to purchase &lt;font&gt;one&lt;/font&gt; share of the Company's common stock (the &amp;#147;Warrants&amp;#148; and collectively with the Shares, the&amp;#160;&amp;#147;Units&amp;#148;) at a price per Unit equal to the &lt;font&gt;fifty&lt;/font&gt; day weighted-average price per share of the Company's common stock on the OTCQB market, for the fifty trading days ending March 7, 2014 (the date the parties first discussed the transactions contemplated by the Subscription), which was $&lt;font&gt;0.3409&lt;/font&gt; (the &amp;#147;Per Unit Price&amp;#148;). The total purchase price paid for the Units was $&lt;font&gt;2,500,000&lt;/font&gt;. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;font style=color: #000000; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;&gt;At January 31, 2015, the Company had unused net operating loss carryforwards of approximately $&lt;font&gt;17,250,000&lt;/font&gt; that are available to offset future federal and state taxable income tax which expire beginning in 2031.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;The provision for income taxes on earnings subject to income taxes differs from the statutory federal rate at January 31, 2015 and 2014, due to the following:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;Pursuant to Internal Revenue Code Sections 382, use of our net operating loss carryforwards could be limited if a cumulative change in ownership of more than 50% occurs within a three-year period.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;On July 13, 2006, the FASB issued FIN 48, subsequently codified in ASC 740, Income Taxes, which clarifies the accounting for uncertainty in income taxes recognized in an entity's financial statements, and prescribes a recognition threshold and measurement attributes for financial statement disclosure of tax positions taken or expected to be taken on a tax return. Under ASC 740, the impact of an uncertain income tax position on the income tax return must be recognized at the largest amount that is more-likely-than-not to be sustained upon audit by the relevant taxing authority. An uncertain income tax position will not be recognized if it has less than a 50% likelihood of being sustained. Additionally, ASC 740 provides guidance on derecognition, classification, interest and penalties, accounting in interim periods, disclosure and transition. ASC 740 is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2006.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;We follow the provisions of ASC 740 relating to uncertain tax provisions and have commenced analyzing filing positions in all of the federal and state jurisdictions where we are required to file income tax returns, as well as all open tax years in these jurisdictions. As a result of adoption, no additional tax liabilities have been recorded. There are no unrecognized tax benefits as of January 31, 2015 or January 31, 2014.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;The Company files income tax returns in the U.S. federal jurisdiction and in certain state jurisdictions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt;&gt;The Company has not been subjected to tax examinations for any year and the statute of limitations has not expired.&lt;font style=color: #000000; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The Company's tax returns remain open for examination by the applicable authorities, generally 3 years for federal and 4 years for state.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
&lt;div id='EdgarSAA123457890000' style=font-family : 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;div style=display: block;&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; font-family: 'times new roman'; padding: 0px;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; font-family: 'times new roman'; padding: 0px;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; colspan=2&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;January&amp;#160;31,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; font-family: 'times new roman'; padding: 0px;&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; font-family: 'times new roman'; padding: 0px;&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: bottom; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; colspan=6&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;January&amp;#160;31,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;13 &amp;#150; COMMITMENTS AND CONTINGENCIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;Legal Proceedings&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The Company's commitments and contingencies include the usual claims and obligations of a wholesaler and distributor of coffee products in the normal course of a business. The Company may be, from time to time, involved in legal proceedings incidental to the conduct of its business. The Company is not involved in any litigation or legal proceedings as of January 31, 2015, which would be deemed material except as described below&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'

 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;Leases&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;On June 25, 2013, and effective August 1, 2013, we entered into a lease agreement for office space located at 4730 Tejon Street, Denver, Colorado 80211. The office space encompasses approximately &lt;font&gt;4,800&lt;/font&gt; square feet. The lease has a term of &lt;font&gt;36&lt;/font&gt; months expiring on &lt;font&gt;July 31, 2016&lt;/font&gt;, provided that we have two additional three year options to renew the lease after the end of the initial term. Rent during the first three year option period escalates at the rate of &lt;font&gt;4&lt;/font&gt;% per year (starting with the last monthly rental cost of the initial term of the agreement, described below), and rent during the second three year option period will be at a rental cost mutually agreed by the Company and the landlord. Rent due under the initial term of the agreement is as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 6%; text-align: right; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; ;font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#9642; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 66%; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; $&lt;font&gt;7,858&lt;/font&gt; per month from August 1, 2013 to July 31, 2014; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 6%; text-align: right; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; ;font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#9642; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 66%; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; $&lt;font&gt;8,172&lt;/font&gt; per month from August 1, 2014 to July 31, 2015; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 6%; text-align: right; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; ;font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#9642; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 66%;&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; $&lt;font&gt;8,499&lt;/font&gt; per month from August 1, 2015 to July 31, 2016. &amp;#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;Effective August 1, 2013, in connection with the Company's entry into the office space lease described above, the Company moved its principal place of business to Denver, Colorado.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;On April 9, 2014, the Company entered into a lease agreement for office and warehouse space located at 4725-4745 Lipan St, Denver, Colorado 80211.&amp;#160; The rental space encompasses approximately &lt;font&gt;3,466&lt;/font&gt; square feet of office and warehouse space and approximately a &lt;font&gt;4,000&lt;/font&gt; square foot yard.&amp;#160; The lease expires on June 30, 2017, provided we have the right to one &lt;font&gt;five&lt;/font&gt; year renewal term, with rent set at the &amp;#147;market value&amp;#148; of the last year of the initial lease term.&amp;#160; Rent due under the initial term of the agreement is as follows:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; text-indent: -18pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#149;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; $&lt;font&gt;0&lt;/font&gt; per month from April 15, 2014 to June 30, 2014;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; text-indent: -18pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#149;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; $&lt;font&gt;2,800&lt;/font&gt; per month from July 1, 2014 to June 30, 2015;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; text-indent: -18pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#149;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; $&lt;font&gt;2,950&lt;/font&gt; per month from July 1, 2015 to June 30, 2016; and&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; text-indent: -18pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#149;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160; $&lt;font&gt;3,150&lt;/font&gt; per month from July 1, 2016 to June 30, 2017.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 100%;&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE 14 &amp;#150; CONCENTRATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: center; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;A significant portion of our revenue is derived from our relationships with a limited number of vendors and distributors. The loss of one or more of our significant vendors or distributors would have a material impact on our revenues and results of operations. During the year ended January 31, 2015, two customers accounted for &lt;font&gt;52&lt;/font&gt;% of net revenues.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;During the year ended January 31, 2014, three customers accounted for &lt;font&gt;57&lt;/font&gt;% of net revenues.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.7pt; padding: 0px; width: 20px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.7pt; padding: 0px; width: 20px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; valign=top&gt;

&lt;p style=margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'

&lt;p style=margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 geneva; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; text-align: left; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; border-bottom-width: 2.8pt !important; border-bottom-style: double !important; border-bottom-color: #000000 !important; valign=top&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; border-bottom-width: 2.8pt !important; border-bottom-style: double !important; border-bottom-color: #000000 !important; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&lt;font&gt;381,248&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-right: 1.15pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-right: 1.15pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; border-bottom-width: 2.8pt !important; border-bottom-style: double !important; border-bottom-color: #000000 !important; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=margin-right: 0pt; text-align: left; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;$&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; border-bottom-width: 2.8pt !important; border-bottom-style: double !important; border-bottom-color: #000000 !important; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'
 times;&gt;&lt;font&gt;440,194&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=height: 13.45pt; padding: 0px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; valign=top&gt;
&lt;p style=text-align: right; margin-right: 1.15pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial; class=MsoNormal align=right&gt;&lt;font style=font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana
&lt;div id='EdgarSAA123457890000' style=font-family : 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Revenue Recognition&lt;/strong&gt;. Revenue is derived from the sale of coffee products and is recognized on a gross basis upon shipment to the customer. All revenue is recognized when (i) persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists; (ii) the service or sale is completed; (iii) the price is fixed or determinable; and (iv) the ability to collect is reasonably assured.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Revenue is recognized as the net amount estimated to be received after deducting estimated amounts for discounts, trade allowances and product terms. We record promotional and return allowances based on recent and historical trends. Promotional allowances, including customer incentive and trade promotion activities, are recorded as a reduction to sales based on amounts estimated being due to customers, based primarily on historical utilization and redemption rates. Discounts and promotional allowances deducted from sales for fiscal years 2015 and 2014 were $&lt;font&gt;668,424&lt;/font&gt;&amp;#160;and $&lt;font&gt;433,745&lt;/font&gt;, respectively.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
&lt;div id='EdgarSAA123457890000' style=font-family : 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top;&gt;
&lt;p style=font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'; margin-bottom: 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE 12 &amp;#150; SETTLEMENT OF LIABILITIES WITH IRONRIDGE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt 0pt 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman'; margin-bottom: 0pt;&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;&gt;Ironridge Transaction #1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;On March 6, 2013, pursuant to an order setting forth a stipulated settlement (&amp;#147;Order #1&amp;#148; and &amp;#147;Stipulation #1&amp;#148;) issued by the Superior Court of the State of California for the County of Los Angeles &amp;#150; Central District (the &amp;#147;Court&amp;#148;), Ironridge Global IV, Ltd. (&amp;#147;Ironridge&amp;#148;), who had previously purchased a total of $&lt;font&gt;1,017,744&lt;/font&gt; in accounts payable and accrued expenses (&amp;#147;Claim #1&amp;#148;) owed by us to various parties, was issued &lt;font&gt;7,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares of our common stock (&amp;#147;Initial Issuance #1&amp;#148;) in satisfaction of such accounts payable and accrued expenses, which amount came off our balance sheet and was legally released. The accounts payable and accrued expenses represented amounts originally owed by us to various creditors in connection with trade payables, the purchase of property and equipment, prior credit agreements, and attorneys' fees.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The shares issued in Initial Issuance #1 were subject to adjustment as provided below: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;From the date of Stipulation #1 until that number of consecutive trading days following the Issuance Date required for the aggregate trading volume of the Common Stock to exceed $&lt;font&gt;10,000,000&lt;/font&gt; (&amp;#147;Calculation Period #1&amp;#148;), Ironridge was to retain that number of shares of Common Stock of Initial Issuance #1 (&amp;#147;Final Amount #1&amp;#148;) with an aggregate value equal to (a) $&lt;font&gt;1,068,631&lt;/font&gt; (&lt;font&gt;105&lt;/font&gt;% of Claim Amount #1), plus reasonable attorney's fees and expenses, divided by (b) 80% of the following: the closing price of the Common Stock on the trading day immediately preceding the date of entry of Order #1 (which closing price was $&lt;font&gt;0.35&lt;/font&gt; per share), not to exceed the arithmetic average of the individual volume weighted average prices of any five trading days during Calculation Period #1, less $&lt;font&gt;0.01&lt;/font&gt; per share (&amp;#147;Share Price #1&amp;#148;).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;If at any time during Calculation Period #1 Initial Issuance #1 was less than any reasonable possible Final Amount #1 or a daily volume weighted average price was below &lt;font&gt;80&lt;/font&gt;% of the closing price on the day before Issuance Date #1, Ironridge could request that the Company reserve and issue additional shares of Common Stock (&amp;#147;True Up Shares&amp;#148;), provided that no additional shares of common stock were requested.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;At the end of Calculation Period #1, if the sum of Initial Issuance #1 and any True-Up Shares did not equal the Final Amount #1, adjustments were to be made to the shares of Common Stock issued pursuant to Stipulation #1 and either additional shares were to be issued to Ironridge or Ironridge was required to return shares to the Company for cancellation.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;The Stipulation #1 provided that at no time shall shares of Common Stock be issued to Ironridge and its affiliates which would result in them owning or controlling more than &lt;font&gt;9.99&lt;/font&gt;% of the Company's outstanding Common Stock.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The Company also agreed pursuant to Stipulation #1 that (a) until at least one half of the total trading volume for Calculation Period #1 had traded, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, enter into or effect any split or reverse split of Common Stock; (b) until at least thirty days from the date Order #1 was approved, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, issue any securities pursuant to a Form S-8 registration statement; and (c) until at least six months from the date Order #1 was approved, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, issue or sell any free trading securities for financing purposes (except for shares issuable to TCA Global Credit Master Fund, LP).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The Calculation Period #1 was satisfied as of June 18, 2013, at which time a final adjustment was made to the number of shares owed to Ironridge.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The final number of shares owed was &lt;font&gt;5,353,512&lt;/font&gt;, resulting in &lt;font&gt;1,646,488&lt;/font&gt; shares of the initial 7,000,000 shares issued being returned by Ironridge and cancelled by the Company in July 2013. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; For the nine months ending October 31, 2014 and 2013, the Company, in connection with the above transaction, recorded a loss on extinguishment of debt in the amount of $&lt;font&gt;1,800,141&lt;/font&gt; and $&lt;font&gt;728,294&lt;/font&gt;, respectively, which equaled the difference in the fair value of the shares issued to and the obligations assumed by Ironridge. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;&gt; Ironridge Transaction #2 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; On May 24, 2013, pursuant to an order setting forth a stipulated settlement (&amp;#147;Order #2&amp;#148; and &amp;#147;Stipulation #2&amp;#148;) issued by the Court, Ironridge, who had previously purchased a total of an additional $&lt;font&gt;1,278,058&lt;/font&gt; in accounts payable and accrued expenses (&amp;#147;Claim #2&amp;#148;) owed by us to various parties, was issued &lt;font&gt;5,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares of our common stock (&amp;#147;Initial Issuance #2&amp;#148;) in satisfaction of such accounts payable and accrued expenses, which amount came off our balance sheet and was legally released. The accounts payable and accrued expenses represented amounts originally owed by us to various creditors in connection with trade payables, the purchase of property and equipment, prior credit agreements, and attorneys' fees. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The shares issued in Initial Issuance #2 were subject to adjustment as provided below: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;From the date of Stipulation #2 until that number of consecutive trading days following Issuance Date #2 required for the aggregate trading volume of the Common Stock to exceed $&lt;font&gt;20,000,000&lt;/font&gt; (&amp;#147;Calculation Period #2&amp;#148;), Ironridge will retain that number of shares of Common Stock of the Initial Issuance #2 (&amp;#147;Final Amount #2&amp;#148;) with an aggregate value equal to (a) $&lt;font&gt;1,278,058&lt;/font&gt; (&lt;font&gt;105&lt;/font&gt;% of Claim Amount #2), plus reasonable attorney's fees and expenses, divided by (b) 80% of the following: the closing price of the Common Stock on the trading day immediately preceding the date of entry of Order #2 (which closing price was $&lt;font&gt;0.32&lt;/font&gt; per share), not to exceed the arithmetic average of the individual volume weighted average prices of any five trading days during Calculation Period #2, less $&lt;font&gt;0.01&lt;/font&gt; per share (&amp;#147;Share Price #2&amp;#148;) and (b) the positive difference, if any, between (i) $&lt;font&gt;1,019,390&lt;/font&gt; divided by &lt;font&gt;80&lt;/font&gt;% of the average of the lowest five volume weighted average prices during Calculation Period #2, and (ii) $&lt;font&gt;1,019,390&lt;/font&gt; divided by 80% of the average of the lowest five volume weighted average prices during the period from March 4, 2013 to May 24, 2013.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;If at any time during Calculation Period #2 Initial Issuance #2 is less than any reasonable possible Final Amount #2 or a daily volume weighted average price is below 80% of the closing price on the day before Issuance Date #2, Ironridge may request that the Company reserve and issue True-Up Shares as soon as possible, and in any event, within one trading day. For each day after Ironridge requests issuance that shares are not, for any reason, received into Ironridge's account in electronic form and fully cleared for trading, Calculation Period #2 shall be extended by one trading day.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; text-align: right; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;At the end of Calculation Period #2, if the sum of Initial Issuance #2 and any True-Up Shares does not equal Final Amount #2, adjustments shall be made to the shares of Common Stock issued pursuant to Stipulation #2 and either additional shares shall be issued to Ironridge or Ironridge shall return shares to the Company for cancellation.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; Stipulation #2 provides that at no time shall shares of Common Stock be issued to Ironridge and its affiliates which would result in them owning or controlling more than &lt;font&gt;9.99&lt;/font&gt;% of the Company's outstanding Common Stock.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The Company also agreed pursuant to Stipulation #2 that (a) until at least one half of the total trading volume for Calculation Period #2 has traded, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, enter into or effect any split or reverse split of Common Stock; (b) until at least thirty days from the date Order #2 is approved, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, issue any securities pursuant to a Form S-8 registration statement; and (c) until at least six months from the date Order #2 is approved, the Company would not, directly or indirectly, issue or sell any free trading securities for financing purposes. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The Calculation Period #2 was satisfied as of September 12, 2013, at which time a final adjustment was made to the number of shares owed to Ironridge.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;The final number of shares owed was &lt;font&gt;5,406,337&lt;/font&gt;, resulting in &lt;font&gt;406,337&lt;/font&gt; additional shares being owed to Ironridge. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; No loss on extinguishment was recorded by the Company, in connection with the above transaction, for the year ended January 31, 2015 and 2014. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;&gt; Ironridge Transaction #3 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; On October 26, 2013, pursuant to an order setting forth a stipulated settlement (&amp;#147;Order #3&amp;#148; and &amp;#147;Stipulation #3&amp;#148;) issued by the Court, Ironridge, who had previously purchased an additional total of $&lt;font&gt;2,499,372&lt;/font&gt; in accounts payable and accrued expenses (&amp;#147;Claim #3&amp;#148;) owed by us to various parties, was issued &lt;font&gt;5,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares of our common stock (&amp;#147;Initial Issuance #3&amp;#148;) in satisfaction of such accounts payable and accrued expenses, which amount came off our balance sheet and was legally released. The accounts payable and accrued expenses represented amounts originally owed by us to various creditors in connection with trade payables, the purchase of property and equipment, prior credit agreements, and attorneys' fees. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; The shares issued in Initial Issuance #3 were subject to adjustment as provided below: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 20.45pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#149; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; From the date of Stipulation #3 until that number of consecutive trading days following Issuance Date #3 required for the aggregate trading volume of the Common Stock to exceed $&lt;font&gt;50,000,000&lt;/font&gt; (&amp;#147;Calculation Period #3&amp;#148;), Ironridge will retain that number of shares of Common Stock of Initial Issuance #3 (&amp;#147;Final Amount #3&amp;#148;) with an aggregate value equal to (a)(i) $&lt;font&gt;2,624,340&lt;/font&gt;&amp;#160;(&lt;font&gt;105&lt;/font&gt;% of Claim Amount #3), plus reasonable attorney's fees and expenses, (ii) divided by 80% of the following:&amp;#160;&amp;#160;the closing price of the Common Stock on the trading day immediately preceding the date of entry of Order #3 (which closing price was $&lt;font&gt;0.50&lt;/font&gt; per share), not to exceed the arithmetic average of the individual volume weighted average prices of any five trading days during Calculation Period #3, less $&lt;font&gt;0.01&lt;/font&gt; per share; and (b) the sum of (i) the positive difference, if any, between (A) $1,358,299.08 divided by &lt;font&gt;80&lt;/font&gt;% of the average of the lowest five individual daily volume weighted average prices during Calculation Period #3, and (B) $&lt;font&gt;1,358,299&lt;/font&gt; divided by 80% of the average of the lowest five individual daily volume weighted average prices during the period from May 24, 2013 to the date of entry of Order #3, and (ii) the positive difference, if any, between (A) the sum of one and a half times Initial Issuance #3, and (B) the number of shares otherwise owed pursuant to the foregoing. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 20.45pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#149; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; If at any time during Calculation Period #3 Initial Issuance #3 is less than any reasonable possible Final Amount #3 or a daily volume weighted average price is below 80% of the closing price on the day before Issuance Date #3, Ironridge may request that the Company reserve and issue True-Up Shares as soon as possible, and in any event, within one trading day. For each day after Ironridge requests issuance that shares are not, for any reason, received into Ironridge's account in electronic form and fully cleared for trading, Calculation Period #3 shall be extended by one trading day. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 20.45pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; &amp;#149; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; At the end of Calculation Period #3, if the sum of Initial Issuance #3 and any True-Up Shares does not equal Final Amount #3, adjustments shall be made to the shares of Common Stock issued pursuant to Stipulation #3 and either additional shares shall be issued to Ironridge or Ironridge shall return shares to the Company for cancellation.Stipulation #3 provides that at no time shall shares of Common Stock be issued to Ironridge and its affiliates which would result in them owning or controlling more than &lt;font&gt;9.99&lt;/font&gt;% of the Company's outstanding Common Stock and with regard to at least &lt;font&gt;5&lt;/font&gt;% of Final Amount #3, Ironridge shall not sell any shares of Common Stock issuable in connection with such amount until at least six months after entry of Order #3.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;We also agreed pursuant to Stipulation #3 that (a) until at least one half of the total trading volume for Calculation Period #3 has traded, we would not, directly or indirectly, enter into or effect any split or reverse split of our Common Stock; and (b) until at least thirty days from the date Order #3 is approved, we would not, directly or indirectly, issue any securities pursuant to a Form S-8 registration statement.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;Until at least 180 days after the end of Calculation Period #3, (a) we agreed that we would not issue, sell or agree to issue or sell any securities to any person other than Ironridge or its affiliates, except for:&amp;#160;&amp;#160;(A) common stock, options or warrants to employees, officers, consultants or directors pursuant to Employee Stock Ownership Plans, or (B) restricted common stock, in transactions with strategic industry, business or operating partners that provide benefits other than the investment of funds, issued at a fixed price not subject to any adjustment, reset or variable element of any kind. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=CursorPointer&gt;
&lt;table style=border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0px auto; width: 100%; cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 align=center&gt;

&lt;td style=vertical-align: top; font-family: 'Times New Roman';&gt;
&lt;p style=margin: 0pt; font-family: 'times new roman';&gt;&lt;font style=font-family: 'times new roman'
 times; font-size: 10pt;&gt; Through January 31, 2015, the Company, in connection with the above transaction, recorded an estimated loss on extinguishment of debt in the amount of $&lt;font&gt;3,931,134&lt;/font&gt; which equaled the difference in the fair value of the shares issued and the obligations assumed by Ironridge. The Company issued &lt;font&gt;3,853,555&lt;/font&gt; shares in August 2014 and &lt;font&gt;5,000,000&lt;/font&gt; shares in final settlement of the transaction on September 15, 2014.&amp;#160;&amp;#160;As of January&amp;#160;31, 2015 there was no remaining liability to Ironridge. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

							function toggleNextSibling (e) {
							if (e.nextSibling.style.display=='none') {
							e.nextSibling.style.display='block';
							} else {
							e.nextSibling.style.display='none';
							}
							}

On September 30
 2014
 Whittle individually
&#148;) filed a complaint against Rohan Marley
 Cedella Marley
 the Company
 Hope Road Merchandising
 LLC
 Fifty-Six Hope Road Music Limited
 and Marley Coffee Estate Limited in the United States District Court for the District of Colorado (Civil Action No. 2014-CV-2680).


The complaint alleges that Whittle entered into a partnership with Rohan Marley
 the son of the late reggae music legend Robert Nesta Marley p/k/a Bob Marley
 to sell premium coffee products branded after the name and likeness of Rohan Marley. The causes of action set forth in the complaint include
 among others
 racketeering activity
 trademark infringement
 breach of fiduciary duty
 civil theft
 and civil conspiracy (some of which causes of action are not directly alleged against the Company)
 which are alleged to have directly caused Whittle and Marley Coffee LLC substantial financial harm.



Damages claimed by Whittle and MC LLC include economic damages to be proven at trial
 profits made by defendants
 treble damages
 punitive damages
 attorneys' fees and pre and post judgment interest.

The Company has engaged legal counsel in the matter. The outcome of this lawsuit cannot be predicted with any degree of reasonable certainty. In the event the matter is not settled
 the Company intends to continue to vigorously defend itself against Whittle's and MC LLC's claims.


On December 15
 2014

 for the County of Los Angeles &#150; Central Division (Case Number: BC566749)
 pursuant to which Sky Consulting Group
&#148;)
 made various claims against the Company
 Mr. Tran
 the Company's President and Director

 and various other parties. The complaint alleged causes of action for breach of contract

 which provided Sky the right to sell Company branded coffee products in Korea. The suit seeks damages
 punitive damages
 court costs and attorney's fees. The Company subsequently filed a motion to compel arbitration pursuant to the terms of the agreement
 which was approved by the court on April 7
 2015. The outcome of this lawsuit cannot be predicted with any degree of reasonable certainty. In the event the matter is not arbitrated and settled
 the Company intends to continue to vigorously defend itself against the claims made by Sky.

							}
